=== Precincts ===

=== Sacred tree ===
It is a large camphor tree with a trunk 8 meters in diameter.{{Sfn|Awakawa|2013|pp=47}}. It is said that it was already a large tree during the {{ill|lt=Muromachi period|Q334845|WD=Q334845|1=Muromachi period}}, and is estimated to be 1000 to 1200 years old. In 2000 ({{ill|lt=2000|Q1985|WD=Q1985|1=2000}}), the Aichi Prefectural Arborist Association conducted treatment{{Sfn|Sakakibara|2004|pp=23}}.

=== Office ===
It was built in {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}}36 ({{ill|lt=1903|Q2045|WD=Q2045|1=1903}}) as the {{ill|lt=Narumi Town|Q11675375|WD=Q11675375|1=Narumi}} government building. {{Sfn|Sakakibara|2004|pp=14}} It was moved to its current location as a shrine office in July of 1931 ({{ill|lt=1956|Q5221|WD=Q5221|1=1956}}). It has been certified as a certified regional building asset by Nagoya City {{Sfn|Sakakibara|2000|pp=89}}.

=== Setsusha ===
Currently, there are the following ten subsidiary companies: {{Sfn|Sakakibara|2004|pp=11}}{{Sfn|Sakakibara|2004|pp=12}}. In the past, there were about five other companies. {{Sfn|Sakakibara|2004|pp=12}}

